  "task": "Run a population of 8 entities for 200 ticks in a 40x30 world with 80 initial resources. Each entity has a genome controlling movement, survival, and aesthetic behavior. A decision function maps entity state + neighborhood to actions (move/harvest/trail/pulse/idle). Score = 0.5*survivalRate + 0.3*beautyScore + 0.2*efficiency where efficiency = avgHarvested/maxPossible. Output JSON: {\"fitness\": 0-1, \"branches\": 1, \"survivalRate\": 0-1, \"beautyScore\": 0-1, \"efficiency\": 0-1}",
  "scoringLogic": "survivalRate(0.5) + beautyTotal(0.3) + harvestEfficiency(0.2)",
